The paper deals with a fading point-to-point link and its performance in terms of average delay and average power. This is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses scheduling policies, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper uses probability theory to analyze the performance, which is relevant to probability and statistics (cs.PF).
